Step-by-Step: Auto Scaling Group with Load Balancer
Step 1: Create an AMI from ExisMng EC2 Instance
1. Go to EC2 Console → Instances
2. Select the EC2 instance you already configured with applicaVon
3. Click AcMons → Image and Templates → Create Image
4. Provide Image Name: e.g., my-webserver-AMI
5. OpVonal: Add descripVon
6. Click Create Image
7. Wait for the AMI to become available (status: available in AMIs secVon)
!"This AMI will be used for launching new instances automaVcally in ASG.
Step 2: Create a Launch Template
1. Go to EC2 → instances->Launch Templates → Create Launch Template
2. Launch Template Name: my-launch-template
3. AMI: Select the AMI created in Step 1 (my-webserver-AMI)
4. Instance Type: t2.micro (or your choice)
5. Key Pair: Select your exisVng key pair
6. Security Groups: Select the Load Balancer Security Group (allow HTTP 80)
7. User Data: OpVonal (already baked into AMI)
8. Click Create Launch Template
!"Launch Template is ready for Auto Scaling.
Step 3: Create Auto Scaling Group (ASG)
1. Go to EC2 → Auto Scaling Groups → Create Auto Scaling Group
2. Name: webserver-asg
3. Launch Template: Select my-launch-template
4. Template Version: Select Version 1
5. Click Next
Step 3.1: Network Secngs
1. VPC: Default VPC (or your exisVng VPC)
2. Availability Zones (AZs): Select all subnets (for high availability)
3. Load Balancer: Enable Adach to an exisMng load balancer
o Select your exisMng Load Balancer
4. Health Check: HTTP
o Set Health Check Grace Period: 300 seconds
5. Click Next
Step 3.2: Configure Group Size
1. Desired Capacity: 2 (iniVal instances)
2. Minimum Capacity: 1
3. Maximum Capacity: 4
4. Click Next
Step 3.3: Review and Create ASG
1. Review all se]ngs
2. Click Create Auto Scaling Group
!"Auto Scaling Group is now ready and acached to your Load Balancer.
Step 4: Verify Load Balancer and Auto Scaling
1. Go to Load Balancers → Select your Load Balancer
2. Click Instances → Target Group → Registered Targets
o You will see 2 healthy instances iniVally
3. Check Auto Scaling Group → Instances
o You may see up to 4 instances if scaling triggers
4. Test auto recovery:
o Terminate one of the instances
o Ader a few seconds, ASG will launch a new instance automaMcally
o Traffic will automaVcally be distributed by the Load Balancer
Step 5: Test the Load Balancer
1. Copy the Load Balancer DNS Name from ALB
2. Open in a browser → You should see your web page from one of the instances
3. Refresh mulVple Vmes → traffic alternates between instances
!"This confirms Auto Scaling + Load Balancer is working correctly.
